javax.accessibility.Accessible, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable
public class AclEntryEdit
extends javax.swing.JPanel

This is the GUI interface that provides a a way to edit an AclEntry AclEntryEdit is simply a JPanel Subclass that is placed inside of a JDialog object so that the user can specify the information that goes into an AclEntry object. An AclEntry object consists of a Principal and the a list of permissions that that Principal has for the resource (TupleSpace) that the parent Acl is protecting. The AclEntryEdit panel will consist of 2 panels. A Textfield to enter/edit the Principal name A slew of checkboxes, one for each possible permission that the user can check to permit operation
